issue_body:
from this issue: https://github.com/arose/nglview/issues/4

```python
w = NGLWidget(...)
w.representations = [
    { "type": "cartoon", "params": {
        "sele": "protein", "color": "residueindex"
    } },
    { "type": "ball+stick", "params": {
        "sele": "hetero"
    } }
]
```

Since user need to specify options to change representation, should we use more complete English keyword? For example: does 'sele' mean 'select' or something else?

In below yang, the uses statement is on the wrong line and causes assertion, which is not very helpful to debug

```
grouping p-group {
      list p {
          key "name";
          leaf name {
              type leafref {
                  path "../config/name";
              }
          }
        //uses config; // this is the right line and compiles fine
      }
      uses config; // his line should be inside the list above, and causes assertion
  }
  grouping config {
      container config {
      }
  }

  grouping name-group {
      leaf name {
          type string;
      }
  }

  augment /b/ps/p/config {
      uses name-group;
  }

  grouping top{
    container b {
      presence "test";

      container ps {
          uses p-group;
      }
    }
  }

  uses top;

```

