DICOM dir files require that the DICOM files names be <= 8 characters and contain only capital letters and numbers (see for example: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5177463/dicom-dcmmkdir-file-name-max-8-characters).

I suggest adding a function that creates these names.

Currently I am using this:
```python
def baseN(num,b,numerals="0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz"):
    return ((num == 0) and numerals[0]) or (baseN(num // b, b, numerals).lstrip(numerals[0]) + numerals[num % b])

def make_dicom_dir_ok(obj):
    return baseN(abs(hash(obj)) % 36**8, 36).upper()
```

