Hi,
by using the function insertRandomNonZerosIntoColumns_() of the SparseMatrix, I have got an error at the line 1046 of the SparseMatrix.hpp, because the variable numRemainingAvailability is zero:
https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/master/src/nupic/math/SparseMatrix.hpp#L1046

after looking at the code, I believe that 
1. it is logical by decrementing this variable will be 0 after some steps and
2. we should handle this cases in another way, e.g. using break instead of NTA_ASSERT(numRemainingAvailable > 0);
Origin:
```C
            NTA_ASSERT(numRemainingAvailable > 0);
            const bool insertNonzero = (rng.getUInt32(numRemainingAvailable) <
                                        numRemainingToChoose);
            if (insertNonzero) {
              row_ind[pos] = *selected_col;
              row_nz[pos] = value;

              --numRemainingToChoose;
            }

            --numRemainingAvailable;

            ++selected_col;
            nextSelectedCol = selected_col != col_end ?
              *selected_col : std::numeric_limits<size_type>::max();

            if (insertNonzero) {
              break;
           }
```
My change proposed:
```C
       if (numRemainingAvailable > 0)
       {
            const bool insertNonzero = (rng.getUInt32(numRemainingAvailable) <
                                        numRemainingToChoose);
            if (insertNonzero) {
              row_ind[pos] = *selected_col;
              row_nz[pos] = value;

              --numRemainingToChoose;
            }

            --numRemainingAvailable;

            ++selected_col;
            nextSelectedCol = selected_col != col_end ?
              *selected_col : std::numeric_limits<size_type>::max();

            if (insertNonzero) {
              break;
            }
        }
        else
            break;
```
What do you think? Thanks..

